    "We adopt the implementation from GEOS library [30].",
    "For 2-D data, octree is also known as the quad-tree index.",
    "❼ UG: a uniform grid (a.k.a., equal-width grid).",
    "The partition number of each dimension is set to d √ N /2000.",
    "❽ EDG: an equal-depth grid index where each dimension is sorted and partitioned into d √ N /2000 parts of equal size."
